---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  pageTitle="Colophon"
  pageDescription="How this site is built - stack, tools, and technical choices"
>
  <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h1>Colophon</h1>

    <p>
      This site is built with <strong>Astro 5</strong>, styled with <strong
        >Tailwind CSS 4</strong
      >, and deployed on <strong>Netlify</strong>. Content is authored in
      Markdown/MDX, managed via Astro Content Collections, and
      version-controlled with Git. Analytics run on a privacy-first setup (no
      cookies, no tracking pixels). Dark mode persists via <code
        >localStorage</code
      >.
    </p>

    <h2>Stack</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Framework:</strong> Astro 5 (static site generation, partial hydration)
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Styling:</strong> Tailwind CSS 4 (utility-first, JIT compiler)
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Syntax highlighting:</strong> astro-expressive-code (Catppuccin
        Frapp√© / One Light)
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>OG images:</strong> astro-og-canvas (dynamic social cards)
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Deployment:</strong> Netlify (edge functions, automatic redirects)
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Monitoring:</strong> Sentry (error tracking), Unlighthouse (performance
        audits)
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Typography</h2>

    <p>
      System font stack for body (optimized for performance and readability
      across platforms). Monospace for code blocks.
    </p>

    <h2>Why These Choices</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Astro:</strong> Zero JS by default, best Lighthouse scores, content-first
        architecture aligns with blog-heavy site.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Tailwind 4:</strong> Faster builds, better DX with autocomplete,
        smaller CSS footprint vs. v3.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Netlify:</strong> Edge-first CDN, instant rollbacks, seamless <code
          >_redirects</code
        > handling for legacy i18n routes.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Performance</h2>

    <p>
      View live performance metrics at <a
        href="https://inspect.trihargianto.com"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">inspect.trihargianto.com</a
      >. The site is monitored continuously with Unlighthouse to ensure Core
      Web Vitals remain within acceptable thresholds.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
